description: Animal (2023): A Son's Descent into Vengeance Animal is a 2023 Indian Hindi-language action drama film directed by Sandeep Reddy Vanga and released on December 1st, 2023. The film tells the story of a son, played by Ranbir Kapoor, whose relationship with his father, played by Anil Kapoor, begins to deteriorate. As the bond fractures, the son embarks on a violent quest for vengeance, undergoing a remarkable transformation. Here's a summary of the key points: Genre: Action/Crime Runtime: 3 hours 21 minutes Director: Sandeep Reddy Vanga Cast: Ranbir Kapoor, Anil Kapoor, Bobby Deol, Rashmika Mandanna Synopsis: A son's relationship with his father fractures, leading him on a violent path of revenge. Themes: Family conflict, revenge, transformation, violence Box office: Earning ₹660.78 crore (US$83 million), Animal emerged as the fourth highest-grossing Indian film of 2023 and the highest-grossing A (adults only) rated Indian film of all time. Additional details: The film is known for its intense action sequences and emotional drama. Ranbir Kapoor's performance has been praised by critics. The film is rated A (adults only) due to violence and strong language. Overall, Animal is a powerful and disturbing film that explores the complex themes of family conflict and revenge.

author: @skmreviewvlogs5896
description: *** Animal Hindi Movie Review *** Starring Ranbir Kapoor in the lead role. Also starring Rashmika Mandanna Bobby Deol  Anil S Kapoor . Directed by Sandeep Reddy Vanga. One Line Review : Family Vengeance Issue Portrayed through Quentin Tarantino style.. Ranbir Kapoor as an animal. An extremely violent version of Ranbir had been showcased here  he fits into these shoes well. Sandeep had taken out his extreme rage character  had made him toiled for this character which we were able to notice on the screen. Bobby Deol comes at the last 1 hour  his contribution had any impact. As his character was a mute person, his impact was too a mute. If it's conveyed in a way that its not always words but sometimes less words more action speaks as a defence mechanism, still Bobby Deol was under utilized. Anil Kapoor whose character is the soul and why this title suits Ranbir's character, had done a decent performance.. Rashmika an Ok performance delivery. But the film which was rocketing high in the first half with a terrific interval block , 2nd half was down with over insertion of family drama, father - son bond, lust, last few hours of streched feel made the movie watching unbearable. Sandeep had taken a told known topic in a violent mode. So it's like a coconut appearing to be tough at out but when broken it's decayed.. Still a 1 time Watchable flick.. 3 / 5 ⭐
